-in-the-French-and-Indian-War-1753-%E2%80%93-1763.pdf","primary_url_label":"Berlin in the French and Indian War (p. 13)","notable_blurb":"Revolutionary captain, father of Emma Hart Willard"},"cross_connections":[{"type":"parallel_careers","related_id":"H00273","display_label":"First cousins — both commanded Connecticut militia in the Revolution.","link_text":"General Selah Hart"}],"documents":[{"document_id":"DOC006","document_blurb":"Emma Willard's 1855 poem names both parents — the most direct portrait of Samuel Hart's character."},{"document_id":"DOC008","document_blurb":"Almira Hart Phelps article on the Hart family, NYGB Record."}],"military_service":[{"branch":"Connecticut Militia","rank":"Captain (Lieutenant at Saratoga)","war":"American Revolutionary War","war_id":"WAR004","start_year":1777,"end_year":1779,"unit":"Col. Cook's Regiment; Berlin militia company","notes":"Lieutenant under Gen. Wolcott's detachment at Saratoga, wounded 19 Sep 1777; captain of the Berlin company at the New Haven alarm, 1779, repelling Tryon's invasion."},{"branch":"Connecticut Militia","rank":"Soldier","war":"French and Indian Wars","war_id":"WAR003","start_year":1757,"end_year":1757,"unit":"Capt. Johnson's Company","notes":"Fifteen days, 8-22 Aug 1757, in the alarm for the relief of Fort William Henry."}],"bio":{"display_name":"Captain Samuel Hart","title":"Captain","first_name":"Samuel","last_name":"Hart","married_names":[],"bio_blurb":"Revolutionary captain wounded at Saratoga"},"residence":{},"baptism":{},"research_tags":[],"research_sources":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[],"quotes":[],"career":[{"role":"First Clerk and Treasurer, Berlin Congregational Church","start_year":1775,"notes":"Withdrew from the Second Congregational Church in 1807 after a religious dispute."}],"slug":"samuel-hart-1738"},"I00034":{"id":"I00034","classification":{"include_in_path_calculation":true,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":false,"descent_from_john_talcott":f